Working with the data and building the first graph(s) a few things came to my mind

  1. Obs 78 is missing a lot of data. Generally, are we going to keep/drop all missing observations for each category?
  2. Is ‘no gaps’ a regular category or more like the NAs?
  3. Is there a preferred way of visualising the results, that is bar charts, pie charts etc.? Also, are there any corporate design elements I should keep in mind (colour coding, fonts etc.)
  4. Do you prefer png or PDF versions of the graphs?
  5. The above figure uses capital letters only because this is how the data was initially coded up. I can change this if desired.
  6. In the above figure some categories seem to overlap, e.g. ‘engagement’ vs. ‘data, awareness, victims, engagement’. Is this OK or should each group count towards its components separately? I think for the ‘common challenges’ the graph in the above design would be very difficult to read:
